text.section:
"Heritage area" means a developed area of public and private uses that:
Ranges in size from a portion of a county or municipal corporation to a regional area with a special coherence;
Is distinguished by physical and cultural resources which have played a vital role in the historic life and development of the community and contribute to the public through interpretive, educational, and recreational use;
Is composed of contiguous or noncontiguous geographic areas; and
May include traditional parks and historic places or property on the national or State register of historic properties.
